---
import EssayShell from "@components/essay/EssayShell.astro";

const title = "Why This Blog Exists";
const description =
  "I wanted a place to think in public about AI, product design, engineering judgment, and the systems that shape how we work.";
const pubDatetime = new Date("2024-07-13T09:12:47Z");
const tags = ["writing", "blog", "personal"];
---

<EssayShell {title} {description} {pubDatetime} {tags}>
  <Fragment slot="thesis">
    <p>
      This site is not a content engine. <strong
        >It's a place to sharpen ideas in public.</strong
      > Some posts will be technical. Some will be product essays. All of them are
      attempts to make my own thinking clearer by forcing it into language.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <section>
    <span class="essay-section-num">§ 01 — The start</span>
    <h2 class="essay-h2">Writing is how I reduce vagueness</h2>
    <div class="essay-prose">
      <p>
        Most ideas feel sharper in your head than they really are. Writing
        exposes that gap quickly. A sentence either holds or it doesn't. An
        argument either survives structure or it falls apart.
      </p>
      <p>
        That is the main reason this blog exists. I wanted a place where I could
        take half-formed intuitions about software, AI, startups, and
        productivity, then force them into something more precise.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="essay-section-num">§ 02 — The scope</span>
    <h2 class="essay-h2">What I expect to write about here</h2>
    <div class="essay-convictions">
      <div class="essay-conviction">
        <div class="essay-conviction-n">01</div><div
          class="essay-conviction-title"
        >
          AI systems and interfaces
        </div><div class="essay-conviction-body">
          How intelligent systems should be designed, where they belong in
          products, and what workflows they change.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="essay-conviction">
        <div class="essay-conviction-n">02</div><div
          class="essay-conviction-title"
        >
          Engineering as decision-making
        </div><div class="essay-conviction-body">
          Not just code, but the protocols, abstractions, and tradeoffs that
          make teams effective.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="essay-conviction">
        <div class="essay-conviction-n">03</div><div
          class="essay-conviction-title"
        >
          Startups and leverage
        </div><div class="essay-conviction-body">
          What creates momentum, what creates noise, and how small decisions
          compound over time.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="essay-conviction essay-conviction-core">
        <div class="essay-conviction-n">Core</div><div
          class="essay-conviction-title"
        >
          Learning in public
        </div><div class="essay-conviction-body">
          This blog is not a record of certainty. It's a record of refinement.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="essay-section-num">§ 03 — The tone</span>
    <h2 class="essay-h2">What kind of writing belongs here</h2>
    <div class="essay-prose">
      <p>
        I don't want this to become a stream of shallow updates. The internet
        already has enough of those. The bar here is simple: every post should
        try to say something clearly enough that it changes how I or someone
        else sees the topic.
      </p>
      <p>
        That means fewer posts, but better ones. More structure. More opinion.
        More attempts at clarity.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="essay-pq">
      <p>
        The goal is not to publish often. The goal is to publish things worth
        returning to.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="essay-rule" />

  <section>
    <span class="essay-section-num">§ 04 — The call</span>
    <h2 class="essay-h2">So this is the beginning</h2>
    <div class="essay-prose">
      <p>
        There will be essays, frameworks, experiments, and probably a few strong
        opinions that need revision later. That's fine. The point is to start,
        then keep improving the thinking.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="essay-closing">
      <p>This blog is a notebook with sharper edges.</p>
      <p>
        <strong
          >I'm here to think more clearly, and writing is the mechanism.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</EssayShell>
